Delphinidae Observation Data (SubjectEvaluation_1R)

Esteban Jorquera

13/9/2019

Human wildlife observations registered from 2015 to 2019 have produced 11843 observations of members of the Delphinidae family, registering locational ocurrence data for 40 species, between 17 genera.

Of the recorded observations, the most common genera corresponds to Tursiops, specifically to the truncatus species. Conversely the less commonly seen genera corresponds to Feresa.
